description:
Job Responsibilities

Develop and implement sales strategy to drive business growth;
Promote medical brand(s) to potential clients in Ethical Sectors;
Build strong network and maintain good relationship with medical professionals and key opinion leaders within the community for lead generation;
Collaborate with customers to create win-win relationship for both parties’ business growth;
Ensure timely and effective implementation of sales and marketing strategies to achieve sales target;
Actively share market insights and collaborate with Brand team to sharpen sales conversion tactics;
Maintain effective communication and good working relations with teammates, Brand team and other related departments to ensure smooth operation;
Provide support for medical conference and seminars and seek for lead generation opportunities;
Work independently with well-planned work schedules and weekly timetables.

Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Pharmacy, Life Sciences, Pharmacology or related discipline;
3-5 years of sales experience in pharmaceutical industry;
Fluent in spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good communication, presentation, negotiation and interpersonal skills;
Detail-orientated, self-motivated, good team player;
Energetic and open-minded;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook);
Less experienced candidate will be considered as Senior Medical Specialist.

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po, N.T.

We offer 5-day working week and an attractive remuneration package. Interested party please submit your resume with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW”. For company details, please visit www.purapharm.com.

Our company is an equal opportunity employer. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, while the personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months after the recruitment process.

Job Responsibilities:

Assist sales team to perform all administration tasks;
Provide administrative support to the team;
Handle general enquires and shop enquiries
Manage day to day operations, including sales documents, proceedings and follow-up
Handle administrative work on data entry and prepare reports to team leaders/ supervisors
System data drawings and analysis (e.g. daily, weekly & monthly report)
Provide prompt customer service support on ad-hoc situations
Others duties/ projects assigned

Requirements:

Diploma equivalent in Business related disciplines;
Proficient PC Applications knowledge on MS Word, Excel (Pivot Table & VLOOKUP) and Power Point;
Strong sense of responsibility, detail-minded. Well organized and able to work under pressure and time constraint;
Outgoing and good interpersonal and communication skills;
Excellent in spoken and written English and Chinese;
Immediate available would be an advantage.

*Fresh Graduate will also be considered.

Sell and promote IT solutions and services;
Responsible for preparing quotation and following up

Requirements:

Diploma / Degree holder of computer science or relevant disciplines;
At least 3 years working experience in IT Industry (preferred in Network / IT Infrastructure field);
Experience in Channel Account Management;
Excellent interpersonal & presentation skills;
Energetic, initiative and independent;
Good command of both written and spoken in Mandarin and English.

We offer a competitive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties, please send your full resume with present and expected salary to us by clicking "Apply Now". 

Website: https://karingroup.com/kesco-it-distribution/

(We are an Equal Opportunity Employer and personal data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities

Perform various sales and marketing activities of a range of frozen and chilled food products in Food Services, HORECA channel
Handling existing accounts and expanding sales distribution channels
Provide before and after-sales services
Keep close liaison with clients
Requirement

Form 7 or above;
At least 2 years of sales experience, exposure in the frozen food, trading or catering industry will be an advantage;
Energetic, proactive, creative and innovative with strong dedication to result;
Excellent communication and presentation skills;
Immediate availability is an absolute advantage.

Please send your application with resume and expected salary to The HR Manager, Dah Chong Hong, Ltd, 8/F, DCH Building, 20 Kai Cheung Road, Kowloon Bay by post or email to click "Apply Now".

 We are equal opportunities employer. Applicants who are not invited within 2 months may consider their application unsuccessful. All applicants may be considered for other suitable positions with DCH Group / CITIC Pacific Group and will be deleted from our files after 6 months from the date of applicatio

Responsibilities:
To expand existing distribution channels and devise effective B2B business collaboration platforms with channel partners for HKMC products including ‘HKMC Retire 3’;
To collaborate and monitor business activities of channel partners and their intermediaries to improve business performance;
To devise and implement an effective operational framework and workflows to work with channel partners;
To develop training plans for channel partners;
To keep abreast of market trends and changes to the regulatory environment of retirement products; and
This is a contract position for 3 years and subject to renewal.
Requirements:
Degree holder or above, preferably in Business Administration, Marketing, Finance or related discipline;
A minimum of 8 years’ solid experience in channel management, preferably in the financial sector;  
In-depth knowledge of financial products with analytical mind and business acumen;
Strong project management, presentation and problem-solving skills;
Detail-minded and able to work independently;
Proficient in MS Excel, Word and PowerPoint; and
Excellent written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).
Candidates with lesser experience may be considered for the post of Manager (Channel Development).



Interested parties please send your full resume stating current and expected salary by 27 January 2022.

Please visit http://www.hkmc.com.hk/eng/careers/job_openings.html for other application methods.

Please ensure that all information provided to the HKMC Group is accurate, complete and updated. Data provided which is inaccurate or incomplete may influence the process and outcome of the recruitment exercise. Please read the HKMC Group Personal Information Collection Statement for Job Applicants at the HKMC website before completing the application form. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.

Associate/assistant manager

The Hong Kong Investment Funds Association (“HKIFA”) is a non-profit-making organization that represents the fund management industry in Hong Kong.  www.hkifa.org.hk.  We aim to recruit a high caliber candidate who will play a key role in the following areas.

The main responsibilities include, amongst others:

lCo-ordinating meetings for committees/working groups;

lPreparing minutes/notes; and providing support to the committees/working groups to implement the resolutions;  

lWorking with vendors to support the maintenance of the website, social media, apps and other relevant communication channels;

lPreparing, managing and updating educational and communication materials (e.g. press releases, investor education materials, communications with members/other stakeholder groups) for distribution and posting on/via various channels; and

lHandling co-ordination and administrative tasks.

Attributes and qualities:

l   University graduate;

l  Solid experience in managing website, social media, apps as well as other communications channels (experience in mainland related ones a plus);   

l   Strong writing skills – both English and Chinese; and

l   Meticulous and have excellent PC skills.

Interested parties please email to Hong Kong Investment Funds Association

 (Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

To provide guidance and support to sales and direct marketing teams on sales governance framework, policies and procedures, as well as relevant regulatory requirements;
To lead and coordinate projects with the objective to streamline sales distribution process flow, and to ensure compliance with regulatory requirements;
To work closely with business partners to maintain existing relationships and business operation processes;
To provide training, product briefing and distribution support to business partners;
To ensure all relevant materials are in compliance with regulatory requirements; and
To perform ad hoc projects as assigned from time to time.
Requirements:
Tertiary educated with a minimum of 8 years’ solid experience in the insurance industry and sales governance as a Team Manager or at Supervisory position;
Strong project management skill and attention to details;
Insurance Intermediaries Qualification Papers 1 & 3 is a must;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, self-motivated and result-oriented;
Excellent presentation, problem-solving and interpersonal skills; and
Ability to make sound decisions to identify gaps and with good problem-solving skill.
Interested parties please send your full resume starting your current and expected salary by 26 January 2022.
